00:49:29,000 --> 00:49:30,000
Avoided by George?

710
00:49:33,000 --> 00:49:35,000
What kind of questions are those?

711
00:49:35,000 --> 00:49:38,000
Why are you acting like that? I'm already in pain here.

712
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:39,000
Just answer.

713
00:49:41,000 --> 00:49:42,000
This might help you.

714
00:49:43,000 --> 00:49:44,000
Truly?

715
00:49:51,000 --> 00:49:53,000
It feels like they are all the same.

716
00:49:54,000 --> 00:49:55,000
But I am more than that,

717
00:49:57,000 --> 00:49:59,000
more surprised by George.

718
00:50:01,000 --> 00:50:02,000
How could he love me?

719
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:04,000
He is my best friend.

720
00:50:05,000 --> 00:50:07,000
Is it really real?

721
00:50:07,000 --> 00:50:08,000
Is he sure?

722
00:50:09,000 --> 00:50:11,000
Oh, maybe it's just inspiration.

723
00:50:11,000 --> 00:50:12,000
We're best friends, right?

724
00:50:12,000 --> 00:50:13,000
We are like siblings.

725
00:50:14,000 --> 00:50:15,000
You really don't know anything.

726
00:50:16,000 --> 00:50:17,000
I am your best friend.

727
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:20,000
George loves you.

728
00:50:21,000 --> 00:50:23,000
Then why didn't he ever say so?

729
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:25,000
That's obvious, Mel.

730
00:50:26,000 --> 00:50:27,000
You are not very smart.

731
00:50:27,000 --> 00:50:29,000
When did George ever say "I love you" to you?

732
00:50:30,000 --> 00:50:31,000
Never.

733
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:35,000
Because he shows it in another way.

734
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:40,000
He is always there for you wherever you go.

735
00:50:40,000 --> 00:50:45,000
He does everything you want even when it's hard for him.

736
00:50:47,000 --> 00:50:49,000
You're too stupid, Mel.

737
00:50:49,000 --> 00:50:51,000
That's why you don't understand.

738
00:50:52,000 --> 00:50:54,000
Or maybe you're too focused on Chanwoo.

739
00:50:56,000 --> 00:50:58,000
The same Chanwoo who once rejected you.

740
00:51:06,000 --> 00:51:07,000
Look at this.

741
00:51:08,000 --> 00:51:12,000
I took this photo while we were watching Chanwoo.

742
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:15,000
Look at his face.

743
00:51:15,000 --> 00:51:17,000
What do I have to do?

744
00:51:18,000 --> 00:51:21,000
I don't want to lose George.

745
00:51:22,000 --> 00:51:23,000
Only you can answer that, Besh.

746
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:29,000
For now, you need to feel everything you feel.

747
00:51:29,000 --> 00:51:33,000
This is very difficult.

748
00:51:38,000 --> 00:51:42,000
I didn't mean to overhear your conversation,

749
00:51:43,000 --> 00:51:45,000
But I recognized my daughter's cries.

750
00:51:47,000 --> 00:51:48,000
I'll take my leave now, Tita.

751
00:51:55,000 --> 00:51:56,000
My child.

752
00:51:58,000 --> 00:52:00,000
What should I do, ma'am?

753
00:52:01,000 --> 00:52:04,000
Love doesn't have to be noisy.

754
00:52:05,000 --> 00:52:10,000
The true measure is when, even in silence, you feel happy.

755
00:52:14,000 --> 00:52:16,000
But I'm confused.

756
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:21,000
It feels like no matter what I do, there's nothing I can do.

757
00:52:22,000 --> 00:52:23,000
There is something you can do.

758
00:52:24,000 --> 00:52:26,000
Choose.

759
00:52:26,000 --> 00:52:28,000
That's not what you want,

760
00:52:29,000 --> 00:52:31,000
but what you don't want to lose.

761
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:34,000
The person you don't want to lose.

762
00:53:02,000 --> 00:53:03,000
Hey, Mel.

763
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:05,000
How are you?

764
00:53:09,000 --> 00:53:11,000
About the last time...

765
00:53:11,000 --> 00:53:12,000
It's okay, sir.

766
00:53:12,000 --> 00:53:13,000
You don't need to explain.

767
00:53:42,000 --> 00:53:44,000
You resign.

768
00:53:46,000 --> 00:53:48,000
And you will leave after this.

769
00:53:49,000 --> 00:53:50,000
So it's none of your business.

770
00:53:56,000 --> 00:53:59,000
Thank you for making my dream come true.

771
00:54:01,000 --> 00:54:04,000
I've been wondering what it would feel like for a long time,

772
00:54:05,000 --> 00:54:07,000
You know, to actually meet you in person so

773
00:54:09,000 --> 00:54:11,000
Thank you for the experience.

774
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:17,000
I will remain a fan forever.

775
00:54:22,000 --> 00:54:23,000
Just a fan.

776
00:54:56,000 --> 00:54:57,000
What are you doing here?

777
00:54:59,000 --> 00:55:00,000
What a jerk.

778
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:06,000
You even dragged your father into lying that you weren't here.

779
00:55:08,000 --> 00:55:09,000
You won't even reply to my message, huh?

780
00:55:10,000 --> 00:55:12,000
You just keep uploading songs.

781
00:55:13,000 --> 00:55:14,000
Why?

782
00:55:15,000 --> 00:55:18,000
I knew nothing would happen even if I uploaded the song.

783
00:55:19,000 --> 00:55:20,000
Are you not happy now?

784
00:55:21,000 --> 00:55:22,000
Happy because of what?

785
00:55:24,000 --> 00:55:25,000
George,

786
00:55:26,000 --> 00:55:29,000
you suddenly confess your feelings to everyone and then,

787
00:55:30,000 --> 00:55:31,000
But not for me?

788
00:55:32,000 --> 00:55:33,000
Why didn't you tell me?

789
00:55:35,000 --> 00:55:39,000
Your song about me became so famous, and I was the last to know?

790
00:55:40,000 --> 00:55:41,000
Would anything change if I told you?

791
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:48,000
Are you here because the song became popular?

792
00:55:54,000 --> 00:55:55,000
Is that how you see me?

793
00:55:58,000 --> 00:56:02,000
George, I have resigned from the company.

794
00:56:04,000 --> 00:56:06,000
I also said goodbye to Chanwoo.

795
00:56:16,000 --> 00:56:17,000
Just answer my question honestly, Mel.

796
00:56:18,000 --> 00:56:20,000
Don't you love your Chanwoo so much?

797
00:56:22,000 --> 00:56:23,000
So what's next?

798
00:56:24,000 --> 00:56:25,000
Are you here now?

799
00:56:26,000 --> 00:56:27,000
What will happen?

800
00:56:29,000 --> 00:56:31,000
Do you know exactly what you want to happen?

801
00:56:38,000 --> 00:56:39,000
I'm sorry, George.

802
00:56:43,000 --> 00:56:46,000
Look, let's take a break first.

803
00:56:49,000 --> 00:56:52,000
Try it first and find out what really suits you.

804
00:56:53,000 --> 00:56:54,000
I will find out if

805
00:56:56,000 --> 00:56:57,000
I still love you.

806
00:57:46,000 --> 00:57:47,000
I will play during the sound test.

807
00:57:48,000 --> 00:57:49,000
There might be a lot of people there.

808
00:58:17,000 --> 00:58:18,000
Coffee latte for Melody.

809
00:58:18,000 --> 00:58:19,000
Thank You.

810
00:58:46,000 --> 00:58:48,000
Miss, may I share?

811
00:58:48,000 --> 00:58:49,000
Oh, this...

812
00:58:53,000 --> 00:58:54,000
George.

813
00:58:55,000 --> 00:58:56,000
I guess you are busy?

814
00:58:57,000 --> 00:58:58,000
I heard

815
00:58:58,000 --> 00:59:00,000
You will go on a world tour.

816
00:59:01,000 --> 00:59:04,000
Hey, you're looking for my name, right?

817
00:59:04,000 --> 00:59:05,000
It touches the heart.

818
00:59:05,000 --> 00:59:07,000
Even if I don't look, you're already famous.

819
00:59:08,000 --> 00:59:10,000
I hear and see you everywhere.

820
00:59:14,000 --> 00:59:15,000
You know, Mel,

821
00:59:16,000 --> 00:59:18,000
Being known by everyone has always been my dream.

822
00:59:18,000 --> 00:59:19,000
Correct?

823
00:59:20,000 --> 00:59:22,000
But to be honest,

824
00:59:23,000 --> 00:59:26,000
There is only one person I want to please.

825
00:59:31,000 --> 00:59:35,000
Until now, you still don't know how to say something directly?

826
00:59:38,000 --> 00:59:39,000
I'm sorry.

827
00:59:39,000 --> 00:59:40,000
Here.

828
00:59:41,000 --> 00:59:42,000
Okay.

829
00:59:53,000 --> 00:59:55,000
My song now has a new ending.

830
00:59:57,000 --> 01:00:00,000
And in this version, I won't let go.

831
01:00:02,000 --> 01:00:03,000
I will not hesitate any longer.

832
01:00:05,000 --> 01:00:06,000
And I will not be afraid.

833
01:00:09,000 --> 01:00:10,000
About what?

834
01:00:18,000 --> 01:00:20,000
By saying that only you are like that.

835
01:00:23,000 --> 01:00:24,000
That it's still you.

836
01:00:26,000 --> 01:00:28,000
That I still love you.

837
01:00:30,000 --> 01:00:32,000
And whatever your answer, Mel,

838
01:00:33,000 --> 01:00:35,000
That will never change.

839
01:01:02,000 --> 01:01:05,000
Love doesn't have to be noisy.

840
01:01:06,000 --> 01:01:11,000
The true measure is when, even in silence, you feel happy.

841
01:01:11,000 --> 01:01:18,000
Not what you want, but someone you can't afford to lose.

